Melt butter in a small soup kettle over medium-high heat. Cook onions and red and green peppers until tender, about 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in flour, then broth, water, and corn. Season with salt, ground black pepper, and cayenne. Partially cover, and bring to boil. Reduce heat , and simmer for about 8 minutes to blend flavors. Stir in cream, heat through, and serve.